	                                 (8am - 12 noon Greenwich time)
@ENDNODE


@NODE Key
@{U}The KEY File@{UU}

The KEY file is a file you get when you @{" registered " link Registration} GS CallerID.
	
The file is placed in your S: directory and is then read by GS CallerID
each time it is loaded. Once you have a key file, you will have access to
several functions that are in the @{" configuration " link Configuration} but are
ignored without the KEY being in place.


Here are the features that are ignored without a KEY file...

   @{" X              " link X}    @{" Y              " link Y}
   @{" BBX            " link BBX}    @{" BBY            " link BBY}
   @{" BBMAX          " link BBMAX}    @{" HISTORY        " link HISTORY}
   @{" SECONDS        " link SECONDS}    @{" FONT           " link FONT

@ENDNODE

@NODE DialButton
@{U}Dial Button or CB Button@{UU}
	
	Here you have two buttons that do the same basic job but from
	different windows...
	
	1) In the @{" Black Book " link BlackBook} you have a dial button at the bottom of
	   the window near the slider. This will allow you to dial
	   the currently selected phone number.
	
	2) In the history window, you have a CB button that stands for
	   Call Back. This will only be active if the number displayed
	   in the history window has a phone number attached to it.
	   If it does, that number id dialed.


	@{fg fill}NOTE:@{fg text} When a new phone number is added to the @{" Black Book " link BlackBook}, it
	      is added as a @{" LOCAL " link LOCAL} number. This is the most likely type
	      of phone call that will come in so I haven't added any
	      way to scan area codes or prefixes to switch the mode
	      automaticaly. I may later do an area code check, but never
	      a prefix check. It would just take too long to scan the
	      local prefixes to be able to keep proper track of the modem
	      when a call comes in. I only have the time between rings
	      to work with you know.
@ENDNODE

@NODE FindButton
@{U}Find Button@{UU}
	
	In many cases, your @{" Black Book " link BlackBook} may get rather
	large. After a couple weeks I reached 73 entries. It can get a bit
	tough trying to find an entry. Especially if you don't leave them
	in the same place through sorting or deleting. This is where the
	find button comes in handy.
	
	This button will search the phone number, name, address (both lines),
	and note fields. 
	
	The information you are looking for should be typed in the text box
	to the right of the find button. When you type something in this box,
	the search starts as soon as you press <ENTER>. to continue searching
	for the next entry with the same search information, you can click
	the find button or press the @{fg shine}N@{fg text} key.
	
	If you want to start a new search with new search information, you
	can again click in the text box and type new information, or press the
	@{fg shine}F@{fg text} key and then type the new information.
	As before, once you press <ENTER> the search will start.
@ENDNODE


@NODE KeyControls
@{U}Key Controls@{UU}
	
    Key     Window       Action
   ------   ----------   -------------------------------------------------
   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} A @{bg background}@{fg text}B     History      Opens the Black Book. You don't need to hold down
                         the @{bg fill}@{fg shine} A @{bg background}@{fg text} key either. That is optional on this one.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} A @{bg background}@{fg text}C     History      Launch the configuration program.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} A @{bg background}@{fg text}D     Both         Dial the current phone number.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} A @{bg background}@{fg text}K     Black Book   Kill the current entry.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} A @{bg background}@{fg text}L     History      Load the configuration file.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} A @{bg background}@{fg text}Q     History      Quit GS CallerID completely.

            Black Book   Quit the Black Book but leave GS CallerID running.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} A @{bg background}@{fg text}S     History      Save the current configuration to disk.

            Black Book   Sort the entries in the Black Book.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} A @{bg background}@{fg text}T     History      Trim the history file.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} DOWN @{bg background}@{fg text}   Both         Move to the next lower entry number.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} LEFT @{bg background}@{fg text}   Both         Move to the next lower entry number.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} RIGHT @{bg background}@{fg text}  Both         Move to the next higher entry number.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} UP @{bg background}@{fg text}     Both         Move to the next higher entry number.

   @{bg fill}@{fg shine} TAB @{bg background}@{fg text}    Black Book   Start editing at the phone number field or move
                         to the next text field.

    F       Black Book   Type in the FIND text box. Search starts when
                         you press @{bg fill}@{fg shine} ENTER @{bg background}@{fg text}.

    N       Black Book   Find the NEXT occourance of the text you typed in
                         FIND text box.

@ENDNODE


@NODE LOCAL
@{U}The LOCAL/LD Button@{UU}

	This button in the @{" Black Book " link BlackBook} tells the @{" DIAL BUTTON " link DialButton}
	how to dial a phone number. There are three settings for this button...
	
	Assuming the phone number you are wanting to dial is (503) 399-7518...
	
	0) LOCAL 
	   Would dial the number as a local number 399-7518.
	
	1) LD 1
	   Would dial the number as a local long distance number 1-399-7518.
	
	2) LD 1+Area
	   Would dial the number as a full long distance number
	   1-503-399-7518.
	
	3) AS IS
	   This one is indended for areas that get the full number
	   from the phone company. Such as parts of the UK.
	   
	   For example. The number might be +46-345-42-2345 (or what ever)
	   and would be dialed just like that with no alterations.
	
	4) X-Index
	   Because many companies and some people have more than one
	   phone line and therefore more than one phone number, this
	   X-Index setting has been added.
	
	   With this, you can have an entry in the Black Book actualy point
	   to another entry. So if someone calls from this X-Index number,
	   the call will look like it came from the number you have
	   cross indexed it to.
	
	   For this to work, you need to place the COMPLETE phone number
	   in the note field. DO NOT add any characters other than digits.
	
	   If you are cross indexing to (503) 399-7518, the note field
	   MUST be set to 5033997518 with no characters added in.
	
	I had thought about making this more automatic, but I have found that
	some areas need to dial the area code even if they are a local
	long distance number within the same areacode. So I left this manual.
	In most cases, the numbers will be local anyway. And once set, you 
	don't need to reset it each time.
@ENDNODE


@NODE Updates
@{U}Updates@{UU}

Here are the three ways I will be making updates available to the public.
There may be other sources for getting updated, but they are not directly
supported by my and therefore may not always have the most up to date
version....

	1) Join my InterNet mailing list. You will automaticaly be sent the
	   new versions as they are released. They are sent as UUENCODED 
	   EMail messages right to your EMail address. Write to....
 
	                TO: filelist@g-world.com
	           SUBJECT: CallerID

	2) Check AmiNet. I will always place my new versions there.

	3) Call my BBS at (503) 581-0067.

Take a moment to read a little about....

    @{" V1.0 " link V1.0}    @{" V1.1 " link V1.1}    @{" V1.2 " link V1.2}    @{" V1.3 " link V1.3}    @{" V1.31 " link V1.31}
    @{" V1.4 " link V1.4}
@ENDNODE



@NODE V1.0
@{U}V1.0@{UU}

This is the fist release of GS CallerID.

Unfortunatly, I had trouble locating a good BETA tester so I winged it.
And this caused a couple big problems that I quickly fixed in the 
replacement @{" V1.1 " link V1.1}.

Features in place: Main history file
                   Basic @{" Black Book " link BlackBook} file
@ENDNODE


@NODE V1.1
@{U}V1.1@{UU}

This replaced @{" V1.0 " link V1.0} and was replaced by @{" V1.2 " link V1.2}.

Due to the lack of a good BETA tester, I missed a couple major bugs that
I simply didn't consider testing. My mistake. Sorry!


                   ----===<< MODIFICATIONS >>===----


  --->         Users can now edit the CallerID.cfg file and have it work!
               There are still some things that will not have any effect
               on the program without registering the program, but at least
               the modem configuration and some other things are available.

  --->         The @{" Black Book " link BlackBook} caused an error if opened
               with no records. So I added my phone number to it as a 
               starter record. Just in case you wanted to get a hold of me.
@ENDNODE



@NODE V1.2
@{U}V1.2@{UU}
	
This replaces @{" V1.1 " link V1.1} and was replaced by @{" V1.3 " link V1.3}.

As the previous version seemed to be rather stable I started pushing
forward onto some of the finer points of the program. But there were
some problems that were semi expected. Compatibility with other modems
and a font problem I am still trying to figure out. But now that those
are fixed, here is what I have added so far...


                   ----===<< MODIFICATIONS >>===----


  --->         Added 2 buttons to the @{" Black Book " link BlackBook} window.

               1) The @{" DIAL BUTTON " link DialButton}. This is used to dial the number listed in
                  the current entry.

               2) The @{" LOCAL/LD " link LOCAL} button next to the now shortened phone number
                  entry slot. This button tells the @{" DIAL BUTTON " link DialButton} how to dial
                  the listed phone number.



  --->         Added @{" three buttons " link 3Buttons} to the history/id window.


  --->         Added 2 entries to the config file.

               1) FONT allowing you to change the display font. 
	                      (this has a problem on some systems) 

               2) DIAL which is used to control the modem while dialing.

 @{" LOCAL/LD " link LOCAL}

  --->         Corrected an error in the GUIDE relating to the disabled
               functions in the @{" Configuration " link Configuration} file if you dont' have
               a @{" KEY " link Key} file.



  --->         Switched the ID detection mode from modem decoded to
               program decoded. It was just getting too compled and
               time consuming to allow the modem to decode the ID
               stream then figure out what format the modem info was
               coming in. The RAW data is more uniform from modem to
               modem. This also opens the door for differant number
               types in countries outside of the US and Canada.
               
               
               
  --->         Cleaned up the FONT problem. Not a perminant fix, but
               a simple quick fix to attempt to clean up the display
               in some cases. The complete fix will be in one of the
               next releases.

	
  --->        Made some additions to the @{" CID " link CID} section of the
              @{" Configuration " link Configuration} file.


  --->        Made some major compatibility enhansments. The program
              should work with ALL modems now. If not @{" contact me " link Contact}.
@ENDNODE



@NODE V1.3
@{U}V1.3@{UU}
	
This replaces @{" V1.2 " link V1.2} and was replaced by @{" V1.31 " link V1.31}.

@{fg shine}WARNING!@{fg text} The Black Book format has changed!
         Use the Installer or run the DataUpdate program
         to upgrade your Black Book from older formats
         @{i}@{b}BEFORE@{UB}@{UI} running GS CallerID.

With what seems to be all the major bugs worked out and a large amount
of modem compatibility built in, it is time to start making the program
look and feel and act more friendly.


                   ----===<< MODIFICATIONS >>===----


  --->         Made the windows stay on the screen!
               What I mean is that if you alter the config file in a way
               that would cause any of the windows to open off the screen,
               rather than giving up right away, the program will now
               try to move the window back onto the screen.


  --->         Added a @{" ShowDate " link ShowDate} variable to the @{" Configuration " link Configuration} file.
               This will allow the current date to be displayed.

  --->         Added a @{" Trim " link TrimHist} function to the history window.

  --->         Added the @{" Sort " link SortBB} menu item to the @{" Black Book " link BlackBook}

  --->         Fixed a bug when deleting records from the @{" Black Book " link BlackBook}
               The syste would get stuck in a tight loop the next time the
               history window opened. (some times)

  --->         Added an installer script to make setting things up easy!

  --->         Added some preconfigured CallerID.cfg files that are put
               in place with the new Installer script. You can also do
               some other configuration in this script. Such as selecting
               your serial card, unit, and favorite text editor.

  --->         Added an @{" ARexx " link ARexx} port!

  --->         Added a few ARexx @{" scripts " link Scripts to get things started.
@ENDNODE

@NODE V1.31
@{U}V1.31@{UU}
	
This replaces @{" V1.3 " link V1.3} and was replaced by @{" V1.4 " link V1.4}.

@{fg shine}SORRY!@{fg text} After altering the @{" Black Book " link BlackBook} file
         For some stupid reason, I forgot to double check
         the sort routine. It scrambles the Black Book!!!

This version fixes that unbelivable blunder. If you haven't sorted your
@{" Black Book " link BlackBook} under V1.3 then you are safe. If you have, I am sorry. There
is no way to recover the lost data.
@ENDNODE



@NODE V1.4
@{U}V1.4@{UU}
	
This replaces @{" V1.31 " link V1.31} and was replaced by @{" V1.5 " link V1.5}.

Many new functions and features have been added. I do belive that all
of the major points I want to cover have been placed in the program
and I can now start working on other things like the configuration GUI
and a couple other projects.

Of course I will fix any problems that people discover but I am sure
that won't happen as I am perfect now. ;^)


With the advent of the ARexx port, it is time to start on some new stuff...


                   ----===<< MODIFICATIONS >>===----


  --->         More @{" ARexx " link ARexx} commands.
               @{" Serial     " link Serial}   @{" SimCall    " link SimCall}
               @{" ModemCMD   " link ModemCMD}   @{" ModemReply " link ModemCMD}

  --->         Added access to the NEW CALL counter through ARexx with
               the @{" GetVal & PutVal " link Val} commands. Use item 15.

  --->         Fixed a problem with reading Canadian CID raw codes.

  --->         Added more ARexx @{" scripts " link Scripts}

  --->         Better multitasking while external programs are running.

  --->         Cleaned up some of the ARexx interface code.
  
  --->         Added a "NEW CALL" and "SERIAL?" status indicator to
               the minimized title bar. You will understand when you
               see it.

  --->         Highly improved Installer script. This will allow you to
               create ARexx scripts as you install the new version. If  
               you have programs you want to run on the same modem as
               GS CallerID, the installer will take care of that for you.
               Also adds a flag to any existing config file that will
               harmlessly update the config with any new flags the next
               time you load the config file.

  --->         Added autodetection for changes made to the S:CallerID.cfg
               file, GS CallerID will automatically read the new changes.

  --->         Added a new flag to the @{" config file " link Configuration} to allow the date and
               time on your computer to be reset if it is too far off from
               the time specified by the phone company. @{" FIXCLOCK " link FixClock}
               @{" FirstRing      " link Rings}   @{" MoreRings      " link Rings}

  --->         Added a @{" Find Button " link FindButton} and text field to the @{" Black Book " link BlackBook} to
               make finding information fast and easy!

  --->         Changed the @{" Black Book " link BlackBook} @{" Menu " link menu} to make the new
               @{" key controls " link KeyControls} work mode logically.
@ENDNODE


@NODE V1.5
@{U}V1.5@{UU}
	
This replaces @{" V1.4 " link V1.4}.

Only a few changes have been made to this version of CallerID. But I have
included some more script files and some sound files.


                   ----===<< MODIFICATIONS >>===----


  --->         Added a disk icon (DISK.INFO) in case you want to store a copy
               of CallerID on a floppy. I may end up going DMS if the program
               keeps growing. (and it will)

  --->         Added a new @{" BBONLY " link BBONLY} mode to the @{" config file " link Configuration}.

  --->         Added a new @{" LOCAL/LD " link LOCAL} mode.

  --->         Added a new auto script called NEWBBENTRY.CID.
               See @{" ARexx " link "ARexx"} for more information on this script.

  --->         Added fuctions for @{" GetVal/PutVal " link val} items 6 and 7.

  --->         Added a new X-Index setting to the @{" Local/LD " link local} button in
               the Black Book.

  --->         OOPS! Fixed a little bug. I had the ARexx command KILL actualy
               named DELETE. It now works properly as KILL like it should.

  --->         OOPS! Fixed a type-o in the @{" DefDial " link DefDial} section of this
               guide. AS IS mode was listed as value 4 and it should really be
               a value of 3. Value 4 is the new X-Index setting.

  --->         Added @{" FAX/DATA " link FAXDATA} support in a limited fassion.
               As well as some @{" Silent Answer " link SILENT} support.

  --->         Noticed that some modems will DEPROGRAM for some reason.
               They drop the settings for properly catching CallerID
               info. So the program now resets the modem 3 minutes after
               the last ring received. Then every 10 minutes after that.
@ENDNODE

